Your damage numbers are far too high though.  A 4,000 point nuke would be insanely unbalancing, particularly if Crits are factored in.  <br>
<br>
You say that these spells are “Group friendly,” but I would argue that an “average” 65 Wizard, with SCM3, SCF3, Improved/Allegiant Familiar, Focus Effects, and KEI, already is “balanced” in a grouping situation.  By Balanced, I mean able to sustain a relatively high DPS over time.  If Wizards already are “objectively” group friendly, then any failure to find groups is a matter of perception.<br>
<br>
Any Wizards, like myself, who began playing before the Kunark era can tell you about “Group friendliness” – perception and reality. In the Velious era, the average Wizard had a real “objective” problem sustaining DPS significant over time.  This was due to the large infusion of melee weapons, into the game, with high damage and low delays, without a similar infusion of comparable caster items across all level ranges.     <br>
<br>
Thus was born the Wizard LFG problem.  The idea for the “group friendly” spell that you suggest was born in this era.  Some asked – “why not make a high damage, efficient, slow casting group friendly spell?”  A good question, but something changed.  That something was Luclin.<br>
<br>
It is probably hard for Wizards who began after Luclin to understand just how different Wizards were as a class prior to Luclin.  Luclin helped to “balance” Wizards by introducing focus effects, AAs, Flappy, and FT items.  PoP introduced some easily obtainable, superior DDs, in the form of new Draughts and Aganrr’s Thunder.<br>
<br>
I guess my question to you is:  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Why</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> do Wizards really need these Uber Nukes given that AAs, Focus Items, the Familiar, FT items, AT and SoS already provide huge DDs and Draughts provide relaibele and efficient DPS over time?<br>
<br>
In the post Luclin/PoP era, I think your large DD are not as relevant as they once were, and perhaps a bit superfluous.<br>
<br>
I do think we need a 2,000+DD base nuke to round out AT and SoS though.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=202120">Torcer Arcana</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arcanist | <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.thebod.org">The BoD</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> | The Nameless<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zerlatikflaimweaver>Zerlatik Flaimweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/28/03 2:07:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26268.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:Problem</span><hr size=1> Well, at the risk of getting Nadiar's ire up, I'm gonna stick by my guns with my comments on melee range.  Yes, you may not be able to turn PoP level mobs, but it's rediculously easy to turn a fire or ice giant if your spells do that much of his hp in one blast.  Some of the post 50/60 crowd is still in family type guilds, while I'm not, I still remember what it's like.  If you draw the duty of helping with the clear for your lower members' Vox/Naggy raid, it can be really annoying to get handed a beatdown by a blue or green mob.  <br>
<br>
Melee range is a liability in these situations, since your tanks aren't all that concerned with why the mob isn't hitting them anymore, just that it doesn't seem to be moving out of the horde of swinging tanks.  If the mob had to at least take 3 steps in your direction to connect, that would let the slower tanks out there know that they needed to punch the taunt key or have the enchanter mez it a second so they weren't going to carry a freshly rezzed wizard the next few battles.  Also, if all battles occur in melee range, how am I going to be able to med?  Sit aggro is a bitch that close in.<br>
<br>
That said, yes these do suffer quite a bit from balance issues.  I'm not entirely sure how to save the idea beyond tweaking the mana vs. dmg aspect some more and possibly adding a lower aggro component to it.  If it cost more, but didn't annoy the mob quite as much as it should, that would still make it viable.  <br>
<br>
Some of the others on this thread have brought up some good ideas though.  I like the idea of group harvest/group flappy-effects.  Part of the benefit of that is it really breaks up the holy trinity aspect of the game.  With everyone getting mana, you move away from the adding another support tank to the mix mentality and actually create demand for casters in groups, so you don't waste any of that mana.  It's always bugged me that there are so few pure caster groups.  <br>
<br>
One possible problem with the idea of a sub-par clarity spell for us is that we end up leaving out mages from the mana regen club. Yes, mod rods are mana regen, and yes they are easily utilized when paired with Phantom armor regens and AA skills.  Problem is that this is essentially banked mana, it's not being created from somewhere like harvest, lich, or clarity lines.  With the time limits imposed on rods and all, it's about the same as our harvest line in terms of utility.  Without coming up with a similar skill for mages, we end up creating a new bottom rung of the mana ladder, and just swap one imbalance for another.  <br>
<br>
I won't argue that we don't need a little extra oomph, especially at the pre-60 stage, though.  Yes, you can get a non-AE group in Seb, Velks, or HS before this stage, but how useful do you feel, and how wanted do you think you are?<br>
<br>
Zerlatik Flaimweaver<br>
Sorcerer of Tholuxe Paells<br>
